Mashup.description: Mashup to add/remove tiles to/from the ThingWorx Analytics Console
Mashup.documentationContent:
This utility is used to add/remove tiles to/from the ThingWorx Analytics Console
. Each row in the table represents a tile.

To add a tile

Specify the following fields
Order: specify an integer number (0 - 1000) to indicate the tile order; a tile with a smaller number will appear before a tile with a larger number.
Label: type a label if desirable.
Mashup or URL: specify a Thingworx Mashup or URL to open upon the tile is clicked.Choose Create Tile
Then  use the Show in Console checkbox setting in the grid: check to show the tile in the ThingWorx Utilities Console.
To delete a tile

Select a row
Choose Delete Tile.

To update the icon, background, or label for a tile

Select a row
Change the corresponding fields
Choose Save Tile
Mashup.name: TW.Analytics.AddorRemoveTiles
